CAVANAUGH v. CALIFORNIA. No. 747,

Misc.

Decided June 20, 1966. Winfield W. Foster for appellant. Thomas C. Lynch, Attorney General of California, Albert W. Harris, Jr., Assistant Attorney General, and Deraid E. Granberg, Deputy Attorney General, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed as moot.
